description: The James Webb Space Telescope has captured unprecedented images of the planetary nebula NGC 1514, revealing infrared-bright rings around a dying binary star system. These detailed observations, made with the Mid-Infrared Instrument (MIRI), expose the nebula's complex 4,000-year history and unique thermal dust emission. The findings challenge existing theories about stellar evolution and highlight the intricate interactions within binary systems.
title: James Webb Telescope: Ghostly dust rings revealed; 'dead' star surprises astronomers

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Shikhar Dhawan has been summoned by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) for questioning in connection with an ongoing investigation into an online betting app suspected of money laundering. This action follows similar summons issued to other celebrities, including Suresh Raina and Rana Daggubati, as part of a broader crackdown on illegal betting platforms and their promoters.
title: Online betting app case: ED summons former cricketer Shikhar Dhawan

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Former US National Security Advisor John Bolton criticized Donald Trump's trade policies, asserting they've damaged US-India relations. Bolton claims Trump's tariffs, particularly the 50% imposition on India, have driven Prime Minister Modi closer to Russia and China.
title: 'Pushed Modi closer to Russia, China': Ex-Trump aide slams 50% India tariffs

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A British woman, Donna Hughes-Brown, faces deportation after being detained at Chicago’s O’Hare, despite living legally in the US for over three decades. Her husband, a former Trump supporter, regrets his vote, blaming the administration's immigration policies. Hughes-Brown, a green card holder for 37 years, was detained due to a misdemeanor from 2015, which her husband claims was resolved.
title: 'Regret voting for him': Trump supporter's British wife faces deportation

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amidst escalating tensions and recent Russian strikes on Kyiv, former US President Trump has reiterated his commitment to brokering peace between Russia and Ukraine. Trump claims to have discussed the matter with Presidents Putin and Zelenskyy, expressing optimism about achieving a resolution.
title: ‘Something going to happen’: Donald Trump fuels buzz on Russia-Ukraine war

author: TNN
description: A TV actor has been apprehended in Pune concerning an alleged rape that occurred at a house party in Delhi's Civil Lines this past August. The 24-year-old victim reported being drugged and gang-raped by a group, who also filmed the assault and threatened to release the footage online if she reported the incident.
title: TV actor Ashish Kapoor arrested in Delhi 'gang-rape' case

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Yuki Bhambri and Michael Venus have advanced to the US Open 2025 men's doubles semifinals, defeating Nikola Mektic and Rajeev Ram. Bhambri, India's top-ranked doubles player, achieves his first Grand Slam semifinal. He aims to be the first Indian champion at the US Open since 2015, while other Indian pairs faced early exits.
title: US Open 2025: History in the making? Bhambri closer to 'dream' final

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: The GST Council has approved a significant overhaul of automobile taxation, set to take effect on September 22, 2025. Small cars, entry-level motorcycles, and commercial vehicles will see reduced GST rates, while larger cars and high-end motorcycles will face increased taxes. This restructuring aims to simplify tax slabs and impact vehicle pricing across the country.
title: Car, bikes GST new slabs explained: Winners, losers, effective date etc

author: TOI Education
description: A United States judge has directed the Trump administration to reinstate billions in research funds to Harvard University. The court found the funding cuts were politically motivated. The administration froze the funds, citing concerns about antisemitism. Harvard sued, arguing the move jeopardized vital research. The judge ruled the action violated constitutional rights. The administration plans to appeal.
title: Harvard wins as court reverses Trump’s $2.6B research funding freeze

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: Mainpal Badli, Haryana's most wanted gangster, was recaptured after seven years on the run following a parole jump. He had been living in Cambodia as a disco owner under a false identity, having fled India with a fake passport and a large sum of cash.
title: Haryana’s most wanted gangster Mainpal Badli who opened disco in Cambodia deported

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Vice President JD Vance visited Annunciation Catholic Church in Minneapolis to pay tribute to the victims of a recent mass shooting. The visit was met with protests criticizing gun violence, while Vance met with grieving families inside the church. He pledged to advocate for policies addressing the root causes of such tragedies, emphasizing the need to focus on the lives lost.
title: 'Protect kids not guns': JD Vance heckled outside Minneapolis church

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Brian Bennett's impressive 81, studded with 12 boundaries, set a record for the highest T20I score by a full ICC member without a six, powering Zimbabwe to 175-7. However, Sri Lanka chased down the target, fueled by Pathum Nissanka's 55 and Kamindu Mendis's explosive 41*, securing a four-wicket victory despite Bennett's batting feat.
title: Record alert! Zimbabwe opener breaks unique T20I milestone of Faf & Babar

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Thursday, rallying strongly on the back of sweeping GST rate cuts announced by FM Nirmala Sitharaman.
title: Stock market: Nifty50 opens above 24,850; Sensex rallies over 500 points on GST rate cuts

author: ISHITA JAIRATH
description: Torrential floods, triggered by a drain breach near the Delhi-Haryana border, submerged Jharoda Kalan and parts of Gitanjali Colony, displacing thousands. Mungeshpur was particularly affected, with residents forced to flee their homes as water levels rose rapidly. Rescue operations were initiated, and a municipal school was converted into a relief camp.
title: Delhi floods: Yamuna swallows homes inch by inch

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistani cricketer Haider Ali has been cleared of rape charges in the UK after a thorough investigation by Greater Manchester Police and the Crown Prosecution Service found insufficient evidence. The case, initiated by a British-Pakistani woman's allegations, was weakened by evidence suggesting a consensual meeting and a delayed complaint.
title: Haider Ali exonerated: Pak cricketer cleared of rape charges in UK

author: TOI Education
description: The University of Michigan has expanded mandatory misconduct reporting duties to nearly all non-confidential employees and introduced an interim anti-discrimination policy for students. The changes, fulfilling federal oversight requirements, aim to strengthen accountability and trust across campus.
title: UMich expands reporting, anti-discrimination rules: Can accountability reach all?

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump warned of dire economic consequences if the Supreme Court doesn't overturn a ruling against his tariffs, suggesting the US could become "unbelievably poor." He claimed trade deals with the EU, Japan, and South Korea might be unwound. Experts believe Trump's statements aim to pressure the Supreme Court by highlighting potential economic chaos.
title: 'US will suffer so greatly': Trump warns of 'unbelievably poor' America

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Cricket enthusiasts will face steeper prices for IPL tickets as the government has increased GST rates from 28% to 40%, categorising IPL viewing as a luxury activity alongside casinos. This significant hike means a Rs 1,000 ticket now costs Rs 1,400, up from Rs 1,280, impacting fans across India.
title: Watching IPL, cricket gets costlier: How GST rate changes impacts sports

author: PRASHANT RUPERA
description: In a Gujarat village, a dilapidated school has become a breeding ground for chess prodigies. Sandip Upadhyay, a dedicated teacher, uses his own funds and initiative to train underprivileged children, nurturing their chess ambitions.
title: Check this out, mate! 200 children in Gujarat village set eye on Grandmasters 's title

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Congress has criticized the Centre's recent GST cuts as belated, arguing the original tax design was flawed. Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced the rate reductions, effective September 22, shifting many items to the 5% and 18% slabs, with some items now at 0% and others at a 40% 'sin tax' rate.
title: Congress 'welcomes' GST rate cuts; but calls decision '8 years too late'

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Runway relief? Man in kurta-pajama squats to pee next to aircraft; pilot’s viral video divides internet

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Top stock market recommendations: Nuvama Professional Clients Group's Aakash K Hindocha recommends buying Dabur, Bajaj Auto, and Amara Raja Energy & Mobility. Nifty is expected to move towards 24900/25050, supported at 24500, while Bank Nifty, hovering near a 3.5-month low, may see a short covering rally above 54100.
title: Top shares to buy: Stock recommendations for today- check list

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: President Trump defended his administration's actions against Russia, citing secondary sanctions on India as a significant measure costing Russia "hundreds of billions of dollars." He rebuked a Polish reporter questioning the lack of punitive actions against Putin, highlighting India's oil purchases and hinting at further sanctions. Trump also suggested the reporter should seek new employment due to their perceived lack of understanding.
title: Trump snaps at Putin question: US prez blasts reporter; cites 'India' to justify stance

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: In 2019, Reese Ketler's hockey career ended abruptly due to a spinal cord injury. Doctors initially feared he might never walk again. Through intensive rehab and unwavering determination, Ketler defied expectations and returned home early. Now, he inspires thousands as a content creator, proving life continues after tragedy and sharing a message of hope and resilience.
title: After paralysis, Reese Ketler hears a doctor’s unexpected message

author: TNN
description: Rising Yamuna water levels caused significant traffic disruptions in Delhi, leading to road closures and diversions. Key stretches like Outer Ring Road were affected, with advisories issued for commuters to avoid inundated routes. While the Majnu Ka Tila stretch gradually reopened, congestion persisted on arterial roads, and restrictions may continue depending on the river's water levels.
title: Yamuna threatens Delhi: From Signature Bridge to Rajghat, fresh advisories issued

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Brokerage firms have issued varied ratings on several companies. HSBC maintains a buy rating on Glenmark Pharma, anticipating IGI to become self-funding and highlighting key FDA clearances. CLSA has an outperform rating on Indus Tower, despite concerns about its Africa expansion and dividend payouts. Citigroup suggests a buy for M&M Finance, noting improvements in risk management.
title: Bajaj Electricals, UBL& more: Top stocks on brokers' radar today

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Faheem Ashraf cleverly addressed Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan's absence after Pakistan's loss to Afghanistan in the tri-series. He emphasized the team's focus on winning, even amidst missing key players. Both Babar and Rizwan were excluded due to recent poor T20I performances, while Pakistan prepares to face UAE in their next match.
title: 'Don't even remember family': Pak cricketer on missing Babar, Rizwan

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Wayne Gretzky, once the undisputed symbol of Canadian hockey, is now being re-evaluated as the sport evolves. While his legacy remains significant, the rise of international stars and Canada's changing role in the global game have sparked an identity crisis. Canadians are urged to embrace a future where their hockey identity extends beyond a single figure.
title: Gretzky and Canada’s crisis: From hero to fading icon - who defines hockey now?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Nodirbek Abdusattorov ignited a pre-tournament buzz by confidently predicting D Gukesh's title loss, adding intrigue to the FIDE Grand Swiss 2025. While Gukesh aims to test himself in the Swiss format despite already securing his title match spot, Abdusattorov's remark intensifies the competition, especially with Candidates Tournament qualification at stake for many participants.
title: 'Gukesh will lose his title': Uzbek GM's latest comment sparks controversy - Watch

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Josh Allen is navigating a new chapter, balancing his NFL career with supporting his wife, Hailee Steinfeld, a global celebrity. Allen humorously notes the shift in attention during international events like fashion weeks, where Steinfeld's fame takes center stage. He expresses admiration and pride for her accomplishments as they both pursue major milestones in their respective careers.
title: 'Nobody knows who I am': Josh Allen on being overshadowed by wife Hailee Steinfeld

author: KUSHAGRA DIXIT
description: Heavy discharge from Hathnikund barrage caused the Yamuna River to swell, crossing the 207-meter mark in Delhi and displacing around 12,000 people. The water level is expected to rise further, approaching the historic 1978 flood levels.
title: Yamuna at 3rd highest level in 63 years, several areas flooded

author: SANJAY SHARMA
description: Thousands of immigrant students across the US are being forced to delay or abandon university as several states revoke access to in-state tuition. The change, driven by shifting immigration policies under President Trump, has led to increased education costs and limited opportunities for students without legal status. Many are turning to online study or entering low-wage work. Legal challenges and federal investigations are also targeting institutions offering tuition support to undocumented students.
title: US immigrant students priced out as states end tuition support

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Rajinikanth's 'Coolie,' directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj, is experiencing a slowdown in its third week after a massive opening. Despite a weekday dip, the film continues to draw audiences, showcasing Rajinikanth's star power. The movie has grossed over Rs 500 crore worldwide, even amid mixed audience reactions, with the director addressing speculation about time travel and cinematic universes.
title: ‘Coolie’ BO collection day 21: Rajinikanth’s action film slows down; earns Rs 1 crore

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: SpiceJet issued a travel advisory due to heavy rains disrupting flight operations in Delhi, warning passengers of potential delays and cancellations. The India Meteorological Department forecasts continued rain and thunderstorms. Rising water levels in the Yamuna River prompted evacuations from low-lying areas, with authorities establishing relief camps and deploying disaster response teams.
title: Delhi rains: SpiceJet issues advisory; urges passengers to check flight status

author: ASMITA DEY AND RUPALI MUKHERJEE
description: Ahead of the festive season, the GST cut on household staples and medicines is set to boost consumption and ease prices. Companies anticipate increased demand for various products, with tax cut benefits passed on through price reductions or increased grammage. This move is expected to energize consumer sentiment, particularly in rural areas, and stimulate growth in the FMCG sector.
title: Gross savings, less taxing; GST rejig expected to revive demand; FMCG packs to get cheaper

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Lalit Modi, the former IPL chairman, admitted to intentionally violating broadcasting regulations during the inaugural IPL match in 2008 to maximize viewership, overriding Sony's exclusive rights. Despite potential legal repercussions, Modi prioritized widespread access to ensure the tournament's success. This decision later led to contract disputes, investigations, and legal proceedings against Modi regarding alleged favoritism towards World Sports Group.
title: Massive revelation! 'I broke every rule in the book,' says Lalit Modi

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Florida is set to potentially eliminate all vaccine mandates, including those for schoolchildren, a move spearheaded by Surgeon General Dr. Joseph A. Ladapo and Governor Ron DeSantis. Dr. Ladapo, a known vaccine skeptic, has clashed with public health authorities in the past. The state plans to form a commission tied to Robert F. Kennedy Jr. to further this agenda.
title: Vaccine mandates in Florida set to end, state officials confirm

author: NAOMI CANTON
description: An Indian blogger, Yogesh Alekari, on a global motorbike tour, criticized British police after his bike was stolen in Nottingham. The theft occurred in a paid parking area at Wollaton Park, with his passport and belongings onboard.
title: Indian on world trip slams UK police after bike theft, says he misses Mumbai Police

author: TNN
description: In Gorakhpur, Vishwakarma Chauhan fatally shot his wife, Mamta, in a public market on Jail Road. The incident occurred after an argument outside a photo studio where Mamta had gone.
title: 'I was very troubled by her': Man shoots wife dead in busy market in Gorakhpur

author: TNN
description: Sebi chief Tuhin Kanta Pandey urged listed banks to strengthen internal controls to prevent insider trading, emphasizing their dual responsibility in safeguarding unpublished price-sensitive information (UPSI) related to both the bank and its client companies. He highlighted that weak controls lead to stock market frauds and stressed the moral responsibility of banks' management in complying with insider trading regulations.
title: Insider trading: Sebi asks banks to tighten controls; UPSI under watch

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Sidharth Malhotra and Janhvi Kapoor's 'Param Sundari' has grossed over Rs 50 crore worldwide in its first six days, marking a significant milestone for both actors. The romantic comedy, directed by Tushar Jalota, saw a midweek slowdown after a strong opening, but faces competition from 'Baaghi 4' which is releasing soon.
title: 'Param Sundari' Day 6 box office: Sidharth-Janhvi starrer shines, crosses Rs 50cr worldwide

author: BHARTI JAIN
description: India's Immigration and Foreigners Act 2025, effective Monday, exempts persecuted minorities from Afghanistan, Bangladesh, and Pakistan—Hindus, Christians, Sikhs, Buddhists, Jains, and Parsis—who arrived before December 31, 2024, from penalties for lacking valid documents. This exemption doesn't affect the Citizenship Amendment Act's citizenship criteria.
title: Relief for minority migrants from Afghanistan, Bangladesh & Pakistan

author: TNN
description: In Panna, Madhya Pradesh, police filed an FIR against ten individuals, including Child Welfare Committee members and officials from the women and child development department, under the POCSO and Juvenile Justice Acts. The action was prompted by the CWC's decision to return a minor rape survivor to the accused's family, leading to further abuse.
title: Minor rape survivor sent back to accused family by CWC, raped again; 10 booked

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Gabrielle Union bravely shared her challenging journey through perimenopause, beginning in her late 30s, and the emotional toll it took. Alongside this, she and Dwyane Wade faced fertility struggles and a miscarriage while trying to conceive. Ultimately, they found joy in welcoming their daughter, Kaavia, via surrogacy, and are now relishing parenthood.
title: 'You just feel defective': Dwyane Wade's wife recalls struggle; opens up about health battle
